<common-name datatype='string'>evgLAS</common-name>
<comment datatype='string'>The &lt;i&gt;evgAS&lt;/i&gt; operon was inferred based on the facts that &lt;i&gt;evgA&lt;/i&gt; and &lt;i&gt;evgS&lt;/i&gt; are adjacent genes, encoded in the same direction, and their products are part of the two-component system EvgS/EvgA. EvgS is the sensor protein and EvgA is theresponse regulator [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/8125343&quot;&gt;Utsumi94&lt;/a&gt;].
&lt;p&gt;
The expression of the gene &lt;i&gt;evgA&lt;/i&gt; is increased under acidic growth conditions in either aerobiosis or microaerobiosis [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23274360&quot;&gt;Marzan13&lt;/a&gt;]. The increased expression under aerobiosis appears to be caused by the transcription factor PhoB [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23274360&quot;&gt;Marzan13&lt;/a&gt;],  but it is not known which promoter, of two transcribing &lt;i&gt;evgA&lt;/i&gt;, is affected by PhoB.
&lt;p&gt;
The transcription of  the &lt;i&gt;evgA&lt;/i&gt; gene is repressed during the first 24 h after the induction of nitrogen starvation [&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/32571968&quot;&gt;Switzer20&lt;/a&gt;].</comment>
